Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.86,0:00:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Dr. David R. Hawkins. I've been a physician for 35 years and a psychiatrist all those years.\NI've worked in the fields of psychoanalysis and psychotherapy and group therapy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:20.50,0:00:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I've done a lot of work with psychopharmacology. I've done research into the nature of\Npsychopharmacology and its relationship to brain chemistry. For years, I worked in the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.93,0:00:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,field of nutrition and its relationship to brain chemistry. For 25 years, I've specialized in the\Ntreatment of the addictions and serious mental disorders. I've been director of psychiatric
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.77,0:00:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,research at a very large hospital. I helped found a very large outpatient clinic that had 2,000\Noutpatients, and I had a very large private practice, a large hospital practice. I lived a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.16,0:01:07.58,Default,,0,0,0,,very establishment life, lived on a very large estate in the east, and had an apartment on Fifth\NAvenue. And so I've lived a conventional and really quite successful life.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.90,0:01:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And many years ago, I became interested in studying spiritual dimensions. I became involved\Nin Zen, and so I spent many years also in spiritual research. And for the last 10 years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.81,0:01:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been focusing on studying the nature of consciousness itself. Now, today's talk has to\Ndo with death and dying, and we call it saying farewell to the body. Sound lighthearted? Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.05,0:01:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that by the end of this talk, you will perhaps view it in a more lighthearted way than\Nperhaps you've been accustomed. And in this talk, I'm not going to talk down to the audience. I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.69,0:02:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,not trying to tailor it to what I expect the listener is going to be able to hear. Instead,\NI'm just going to talk about what I've learned in all of my personal experience and clinical
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.53,0:02:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,research. I'm going to share with you experiences that I've had, and I'm going to share with you\Nexperiences in a way that perhaps you haven't been shared with before. I've done this with other
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.80,0:02:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,audiences, and people have said, well, you can't talk about things like that. These audiences are\Nnot that sophisticated. They're not going to get it, etc. On the contrary, I found that audiences
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,that people in the consciousness and spiritual were considered naive got it right away. They\Ndidn't have the slightest problem. They all said, oh, yeah, we see it, of course. Everybody felt
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.58,0:02:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,higher. Everybody felt glad. No problem. And so I'm going to tell it to you today. I'm going to\Ntell you just how it really is and how I've experienced it and what has come into my own
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.77,0:02:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness. And in doing so, I'm going to refer to a map of consciousness, a field of consciousness\Nthat we have laid out in sort of a mathematical style. It's here on the blackboard, and although
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.15,0:03:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,it may look complicated at first when I explain it, you'll see that it's relatively simple.\NBecause when we're talking about death and dying, we're talking about consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.23,0:03:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is what people really fear. What people really fear are two things.\NOne is the physical death experience itself, and the other is what they fantasy to be a loss of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.93,0:03:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,awareness, a loss of consciousness, a loss of awareness of existence. By the time we get through\Ntalking about these things, I hope we will have handled those things. And so we're going to refer
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.43,0:03:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to this board, and on this board we have here what's called level of consciousness. This is\Nwhat we call the box. This is the human ego, the self with a small s.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.93,0:03:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What we commonly refer to as me or myself. And at the bottom you'll see we have these calibrated\Nwith death, physical death at zero, and we have at the very top of the scale, enlightenment at 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.18,0:04:10.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we do that, we find in the middle there's a level called courage. And below courage,\Nthe arrows of all these feeling states are in a negative direction. And they're calibrated as to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.18,0:04:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,their relative energy.\NAnd so they're relative power. So you'll see, for instance, that apathy has roughly half the power of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.06,0:04:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,fear, which is calibrated at 100. Fear has roughly the power of courage at 200. Courage has much less\Npower than love, which is at 500. And so these have relative energies based on, as you can very well
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.80,0:04:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,see, these are lower states of consciousness. Guilt, you see, is reversed, and it's only 30.\NApathy,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.12,0:04:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,fear, hopelessness is 50. Regret and grief is 75. Fear and its forms of worry and anxiety is 100.\NCravingness, wantingness, desiringness is 125. Anger goes up to 150. Pride goes up to 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.30,0:05:11.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And then by virtue of telling the truth, in this case it is the truth about life,\Nto tell the truth about life, that life comes from life, a very important statement. Sounds banal on
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.90,0:05:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the surface.\NBut you'll see most of the fears of death are coming out of the failure to get, that life comes from
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.20,0:05:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\NAnd once we tell the truth about it, once we tell the truth about it, you'll see that the reverse,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.69,0:05:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the negative energy field goes neutral. It then begins to go to the right. It goes in a positive\Ndirection. And as we move towards the source of life, the conscious awareness of the source of
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.35,0:05:42.37,Default,,0,0,0,,life itself, we move into higher states of love and higher states of joy. And then we come up to a\Nlevel at about 600.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.39,0:06:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And at 600, there is a transition into a different paradigm, a different experience of existence, in which\None no longer identifies with a separate individual physical body. The person begins to realize the truth of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.53,0:06:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,who they are. The expansion of consciousness goes beyond the individual small self. And so, to the right of\Nthese levels of consciousness, we see an emotion that goes with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.13,0:06:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We see at the bottom with guilt goes self-hatred. And we see a process going on in consciousness that it is a\Ndestructive direction. We see that apathy is associated with hopelessness and despair. And we see that the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.55,0:06:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,process is loss of energy. We see that grief is associated with regret and loss and despondency. And the\Nprocess there is to become dispirited. We see that fear is associated with worry and anxiety.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.39,0:07:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,We see that fear has to do with the future. So, in that, the process is one of deflation. What we are talking about then,\Ngenerally, when people think of death is guilt, and they think of grief, and they think of fear. They may even move up to a higher
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.43,0:07:12.49,Default,,0,0,0,,state called anger, being angry about the whole experience and resent it, be full of hate and grievances about it. As we\Nmove up the energy scale,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.96,0:07:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,we come to a level called pride.\NCalibrates at 175.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.21,0:07:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Pride feels a lot better than these lower states. But, unfortunately, with pride goes denial.\NAnd then talking about death today, we're going to have to overcome some of this denial.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.85,0:07:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The denial is really coming up because of fear, once what is fear is understood, then denial drops out and one can move up and move up to the level of courage.\NCourage,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.33,0:07:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you see,\Nenergy field goes neutral now, it has a lot more power. The energy field of courage is enough to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.35,0:07:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,settle the United States of America and create the huge industries and sciences. That's the energy\Nfield that takes man to the moon. So it is the capacity then emotionally to face, to cope, to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.73,0:08:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,handle. And once you begin to tell the truth about things, you become empowered. Empowered.\NThat moves you up to a state of willingness, the willingness to get what is the truth about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.59,0:08:25.63,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that happens at this, you see, we've left the denial of the arrogance of pride because\Npride is associated with arrogance, thinking I know when in reality you don't know, pretending to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.63,0:08:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,know, coming from beliefs and opinions which are somebody else's thoughts that you have gathered\Nto yourself and now your ego has taken a position about and you feel you must defend those. To let
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.11,0:08:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,go of that arrogance, we can move up then to willingness. We say, yes, I want to know what is\Nthe truth about the matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.83,0:08:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,For my own sake. It becomes powerful because now your intention is put into the energy field. You\Nbegin to move up to wanting to know more about a thing and the capacity to accept. You see, down
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.65,0:09:11.20,Default,,0,0,0,,here you've given your power away. You've said, I don't have the capacity. I don't have the power. I\Ndon't have the ability to get what this is all about. I have to rely on tradition and folklore
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.20,0:09:18.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and all that kind of thing.\NThe willingness to look into the matter then gives you an open mind and the open mind then
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.29,0:09:29.87,Default,,0,0,0,,moves you up to a state called acceptance, which means you've begun to reown your power. These\Nstates from here to down here, you've given your power away. You've given your survival to
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.87,0:09:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,something outside of yourself. And as you reown that power, you begin to feel adequate and\Nconfident. And there's the beginning in consciousness of transformation. The awareness
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.37,0:09:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,am the source of my own happiness,\Nthat I have the capacity to find out the truth for myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.49,0:09:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,And you move up to an energy field of 500 called lovingness.\NLovingness, that capacity, that dedication
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.83,0:10:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,to nurturing, supporting life,\Nthe willingness to be forgiving.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.53,0:10:08.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And with that begins a certain revelation\Nabout an energy field that we calibrated around 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.51,0:10:14.49,Default,,0,0,0,,540 is associated with healing,\Nhealing with gratitude.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.51,0:10:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can move up to an energy field called joy.\NJoy, and it calibrates here at about 540.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.55,0:10:28.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And inner serenity,\Nand what really characterizes it is compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.39,0:10:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Compassion, the ability to see into the hearts of others,\Nthe willingness to be love,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.26,0:10:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,nonjudgmental to life itself\Nand all of its expressions.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.72,0:10:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,At about 560, we come to an energy field,\Nwhich I didn't write on the board
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.62,0:10:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's too crowded as it is,\Ncalled ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.74,0:10:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a jumping up and down with,\Nthese are not jumping up and down states,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.84,0:10:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,not jumping up and down with joy,\Nnot jumping up and down with ecstasy,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,but an inner state as you're beginning\Nto approach the truth of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.92,0:11:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,an inner ecstatic state which is quiet\Nand gradually moves up to a state called peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.06,0:11:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the peace of God.\NThe emotion going with that is bliss,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.32,0:11:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person is really going into states of illumination.\NAnd many people, as they go into this state,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.96,0:11:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,feel as though a light is,\Nthey're encompassed within a light,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.88,0:11:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,that they are that light.\NAnd then when we go up to 600,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.64,0:11:32.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the top of the box here is 600,\Nat that point, the identification with the personal self stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.68,0:11:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,One goes into an ineffable state,\Na state that is so exquisite it is difficult to describe.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.45,0:11:45.37,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens with your relationship\Nat that point with the body?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.03,0:11:50.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What actually happens is you forget the body.\NYou just forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.03,0:11:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,You forget that it is, was, exists, or existed.\NThere is really no memory of the body anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.91,0:12:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,because the body is associated with an identification\Nwith the personal separate self.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.70,0:12:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That identification limited your consciousness\Nand your awareness to that identification
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.08,0:12:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,with the physical body,\Nand people then think,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.48,0:12:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,well, how can I go on living in that body?\NAnd as you reach more enlightened states,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.55,0:12:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as people really approach death,\Npeople who have any preparation for it at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.53,0:12:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,instead there is an exquisite expansion of consciousness,\Na loss of identification with that body
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.87,0:12:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and the personal self.\NAnd then we go up into the energy fields above the 600s.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.47,0:12:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Those are states of feeling of oneness and completeness\Nand wholeness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.99,0:12:49.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and oneness with all of life,\Nand oneness with God. These levels of consciousness are also associated, as you will see, with
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.57,0:13:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,they dominate your view of the world, your view of life, and they dominate your view\Nof God. And so we will say a little something about them. You will see that the guilty person
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.96,0:13:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,sees this as a world of sin and suffering, and therefore the God of that world would\Nbe a destroyer. We see that the person who is coming from hopelessness, apathy, sees
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.67,0:13:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,this as a hopeless world and thinks that God must be dead. The person who is coming\Nfrom grief, feels neglected and forgotten by God, sees this as a sad world and feels
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.60,0:13:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that God ignores you because you are such a worthless worm. The person who comes from\Nfear, then, sees this as a frightening world, and therefore God would be the most frightening
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.93,0:13:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of all possible experiences. The person who is coming from craving and desiring sees this\Nas a frustrating world, and therefore the God of that world would be a destroyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.05,0:13:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The God of anger, I mean the person living out of anger, sees this as a competitive,\Nangry world of conflict and war. And consequently the God that would be expected from that level
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.51,0:14:11.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness is a retaliatory God of revenge. The person in pride sees this world as a world\Nof status, and because of their arrogance, intellectual arrogance, may end up either
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.19,0:14:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as atheist or bigot, the zealot, who feels that I am right and the world is wrong. All\Nof this leaves us in very difficult positions. As we move out of pride, we move up to a level
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.76,0:14:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,called courage. That is the capacity to face things for the first time. We see the direction\Nof the arrow went neutral, meaning that that which is negative, that which is a lie, all
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.46,0:14:46.79,Default,,0,0,0,,of this down here is that which is not true, that the energy field is changing. And when\Nwe do, our view of the world changes dramatically. From a negative view of the world, from a
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.79,0:14:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,negative experience of the world, we now see this as a challenging world of excitement\Nand opportunity. By the time we get through talking about death, we will be at least up
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.31,0:15:10.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to this. That is the most exciting opportunity you have had thus far.\NIt is characterized this state then by an open mind. It means I don't really know. Open
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.02,0:15:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,mind says question mark.\Nsays for the first time what is the truth please lord let me open my mind and know what is the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.80,0:15:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,truth for my own self know within my own consciousness to know where i know things\Nwe move above neutral then i mean we move out of courage we move up to a level called neutral
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.90,0:15:44.05,Default,,0,0,0,,here you see the error goes positive our energy field has jumped to 250 and what characterizes\Nthat is detached unattached the person now experiences that they are released released
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.05,0:16:00.29,Default,,0,0,0,,from all this negativity down here a person at this level sees the world as okay would see all\Nexperiences that would include death as okay and experiences god therefore as freedom you see the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.29,0:16:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,loss of fear of god the loss of guilt the loss of expecting god to be the great avenger and\Nthe person will become generate that thing again and do it with all that from the head the PlayStation
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.07,0:16:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,person coming out of jealousy and hate. The god of hatred is down here who hates man and hates\Nman's humanness. All a paradox in as much as God created us. Anyway, we move up then to what is the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.96,0:16:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, the willingness to look at what is the truth. And here, because of our open mind, our\Nwillingness now to investigate what is the truth of it, we begin to experience life as friendly,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.84,0:16:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,life and the world and all the experiences in the world, including the death experience,\Nwe now expect it to be some kind of a positive experience. And God now becomes promising and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.40,0:16:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,hopeful. It's like we look forward to death as some kind of a great release into a much greater\Nexpansion in consciousness and awareness. As we move out of acceptance, which we do by owning
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.29,0:17:05.81,Default,,0,0,0,,back our own power to know, we move into a loving state, that which is forgiving,\Nthat which is a strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.81,0:17:11.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We move back to a loving state where we are one and the same and the result of that recovery is\Nwhich is understanding, the beginning of revelation, and now we begin to experience all of life
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.99,0:17:18.01,Default,,0,0,0,,in a loving way.\NWe begin to see the love that's present everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.01,0:17:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore we move into a God that is merciful, and out of mercy we see unconditional love.\NWe now expect a God who is unconditionally loving, God and all His representatives, all
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.35,0:17:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,His representatives.\NThe realization of the lovingness that that is the basic reality moves you to an inner
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.79,0:17:47.41,Default,,0,0,0,,state of joy.\NOut of that comes compassion, the transfiguration of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.41,0:17:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We begin to see the perfection of all of creation, the incredible beauty.\NWe see the oneness of all of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.37,0:18:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And as we move towards the top of the box we move into states which we call bliss.\NStates of enlightenment.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.71,0:18:10.45,Default,,0,0,0,,In\Nillumination in which we then become conscious and aware of that unity that oneness that beingness
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.21,0:18:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,at that point as we said you move out of the ordinary energy fuels of ordinary consciousness\Nand you move up into energy fuels which we calibrate in the 600s and something there
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.82,0:18:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,strange happens there this is a point where many people have amnesia\Nbecause they're so habituated to thinking of themselves as an individual physical body that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.29,0:18:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,anything other than that is relegated to amnesia and but as you go beyond that as you go into states\Nof that the world calls enlightenment which is just really another paradigm another way of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.93,0:18:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing existence and life at about 615 or so there's the capacity to remember the death\Nexperience to know what it is
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.97,0:19:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to recall all the times that it occurred with a conscious awareness and as we go up to states that\Nare higher than that in the mid 600s and all we reach more advanced states of awareness and
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.48,0:19:24.63,Default,,0,0,0,,consciousness and so i'm going to share with you today things that i've learned clinically over\Nthat many years of experience things that i personally experienced myself and we'll talk now
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.63,0:19:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,from having a field of reference about what the\Ndeath experience really entails and so and going back then i'll be going back to childhood in my
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.27,0:19:47.58,Default,,0,0,0,,own experience and so i'll start telling you about some things that happened in my life\Nand then how it fit in with things that happened later on when i was about 14 i was a paper boy in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.58,0:20:00.22,Default,,0,0,0,,northern wisconsin and it was about 20 below zero in a weather and the weather was about 20 below\Nzero and i was practically freezing to death so i mean literally and i what i did was i went to a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.22,0:20:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,school in northern wisconsin and i went to a school in northern wisconsin and i went to a snow bank\Nand i crawled inside of this cubby hole that i dug and the snow was piled about 20 feet high on the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.08,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,side of the highways there and i crawled into this little cubby hole and cuddled up in order just to\Nget out of the wind which was really fierce and terrible and within a few seconds i began to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,experience a state of relaxation a state of profound warmth began to overcome me and my body\Nthe body, the state of almost exquisite pleasure. I began to forget about the body. The body just
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.27,0:20:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't seem to exist anymore. And instead this incredible state overcame me. It was like\Nsurrounded by light, but the light had a quality of touching you and being with you as though it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.23,0:21:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,was a loving consciousness that was enveloping you and dissolving so that you dissolved and\Nbecame this infinite field that had no beginning and no end. It had no dimension. It was outside
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.57,0:21:27.49,Default,,0,0,0,,of time. The experience could have lasted for seconds or eons in earth time. It made no difference\Nbecause once having experienced it, the experience was total. At every instant the experience was
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.49,0:21:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,total and complete.\NThere was nothing missing, nothing lacking, nothing further to be accomplished. And there
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.53,0:21:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,was a profound state of peace that is beyond description. At first as it came on there was\Nthis inner feeling of relief, an inner feeling of relief, and then an inner feeling of a quiet joy,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.48,0:21:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and then the inner feeling of a quiet ecstasy, and then it went beyond ecstasy. It went beyond bliss.\NIt became an infinite state which
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.20,0:22:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not within ordinary consciousness. Sometime later, it could have been 15 minutes, half an hour,\NI felt someone shaking me and I was like forcibly pulled out of this state. My father was shaking
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.86,0:22:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,me and he had a very upset, anxious look on his face. And he said, don't you ever do that again,\Ndon't you know you can freeze to death? I had no context in which to hold this experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.43,0:22:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what its meaning was. It had just been\Na profound experience and in the mind of a child there was really nothing to say about it. I might
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.53,0:22:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,have mentioned something to it as I think it did perhaps mention something about it to my father,\Nbut he didn't have any way in which to hold it either and besides he was frightened at the time
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.95,0:23:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and so neither of us knew what the experience meant. Neither of us realized what was being\Nsignified. At that time there were no books on the near-death experiences. The movie Resurrection
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.11,0:23:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,has only come out in the last 10 years. That movie Resurrection, by the way, was clinically accurate.\NThose who have had that kind of experience all verify the truth of what she experienced. You
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.47,0:23:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,know, she got killed in an automobile accident. It's a true story of an actual person who was\Ndeclared dead on the operating table and she left the body, she experienced the death of her husband,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.45,0:23:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,she experienced that same incredible infinite state. My father and I not knowing of these things\Nhad no context in which to hold this experience, no way of understanding it and so although I
Dialogue: 0,0:23:44.23,0:23:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,mentioned it briefly to him, he didn't know what to make of it either and besides he was\Ntoo frightened at the time and so the experience was never mentioned again and neither did I ever
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.47,0:24:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,understand it over the coming years until I got older.\NThen I was dying of a very serious and progressive ailment back in my 30s and as I was laying in this
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.84,0:24:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,bed in a very moribund condition and in a grave state, I will tell you, all of a sudden, much to\Nmy surprise, there I was about 10 feet over the body, about 8 feet over the physical body. There
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.75,0:24:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a perfect body exactly like this one. It looked exactly the same except that it seemed to\Nbe weightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.18,0:24:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Practically weightless. In fact, it was weightless and I had all my faculties. I could think and\Nreason and see and hear and I looked down at the physical body that was lying in the bed about 8 or
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.90,0:24:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,10 feet below me and you know, he looked like he was about to go and here I was outside the physical\Nbody looking down at it, you see, aware that that which I am is something other than the physical
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.46,0:25:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,body. At that time, I'd never heard of out-of-body experiences and it's only in the last five or\N10 years that a lot of books, well, there are classics written and almost in Victorian times,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.86,0:25:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but they were known only to a very limited number of people. But now, there's all kinds of bodies\Nand surveys now show that something like 65% of the population has had these, consciously
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.64,0:25:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,remembers these kind of experiences. And so therefore, what I'm saying today is, you know,\Nnot shocking like it would have been perhaps years ago. But there I was in a grave illness and I found
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.10,0:25:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,myself totally out of the body and it was not time for me to leave and so at a later point, I had to\Nre-enter the body again. Later on, I learned that this was a technique that one could do this at
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.75,0:25:58.17,Default,,0,0,0,,will. I learned that there's all kinds of people who leave the body at will. There's people who\Nare born with this gift and there are people who are very right-brained and they sit down to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.17,0:26:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,meditate and as soon as they sit down to meditate, they have this experience. Well, I was a left-brain\Nscientist, a skeptic, a pragmatist and I became very curious about this phenomena and so I found
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.75,0:26:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that there was a scientifically oriented place that where this is being studied. And so I read\Nthe book out of, you know, Journeys Out of the Body by Robert Monroe and I went to the Monroe
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.81,0:26:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Institute and there I did a 10-day training, 10-day training where they have audio tapes\Nand the frequency, the difference of the frequency between the two ears creates
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.87,0:26:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,a frequency that entrains the brain and within that certain altered state of consciousness,\None can leave the body at will. So I learned that this is a state then that people who aren't born
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.57,0:26:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with this capacity or who don't develop it spontaneously can later learn to do at will.\NThe purpose of that was merely my own learning that you are something other than the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.67,0:27:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,that that which you are is greater than the physical body, that the physical body belongs\Nto you but that you are not that. So I recovered from that particular episode of the illness and
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.96,0:27:24.06,Default,,0,0,0,,continued to live and the illness, however, relapsed and it got worse again. This time it\Nwas grave indeed and I was really right at the very door of death itself. I was in a state of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.06,0:27:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,grave, almost a state of hell, a state of absolute and total helplessness, hopelessness, despair,\Nself-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.32,0:27:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in a state of complete malice till the bottom of the box and about a couple of them,\Nreally just a few seconds away from what would really be leaving the body again,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.30,0:27:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked, I was an Atheist at the time and had been an Atheist for some twenty years. Despite\Nthese experiences of an infinite beingness, I still in the face of it, you see the character
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.88,0:28:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of pride is arrogance and denial see, denial and arrogance. Despite having had these incredible\Nexperiences, I was something other than hell-like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.06,0:28:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,than the body, I still didn't have a way in which to hold it. And I was still an\Natheist, and here I was dying of this disease, and really in the last few
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.07,0:28:26.44,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes, and when I suddenly said, you know, if there is a God, I asked him to\Nhelp me. And then I went unconscious. I don't remember a thing. And when I became
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.44,0:28:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,conscious again, there I was out, you might say, outside the box. I'd gone up to\Na field of consciousness, which is up here off the blackboard. And there was no
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.16,0:28:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,longer any identification with this personal physical body. It walked around\Nand it did all the things it's supposed to. But I stood in an energy field that
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.28,0:29:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,was so infinite. The power and the dimension of the field was beyond\Ndescription. It held me in absolute safety. It was like rock. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.61,0:29:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,is at the same time exquisitely soft and gentle.\NIts exquisite gentleness and its exquisite softness
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.31,0:29:18.86,Default,,0,0,0,,held me in its infinite embrace,\Nand it spoke through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.86,0:29:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The body just did what the infinite will,\Nhow it expressed itself through this personal,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.16,0:29:33.86,Default,,0,0,0,,or what was still left of the personal self.\NAnd so I walked around in that state for some months,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.86,0:29:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,for some months, and I still didn't really have a context\Nin which to hold it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.78,0:29:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There was nothing much you could say about it.\NI think the only way I expressed it to someone in my life at that time,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.74,0:29:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, when I was at the bottom of the box,\NI was like an absolute blackness, totally cut off from God.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.10,0:30:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And now it's like that which stood between me and God has been removed,\Nand I'm now standing in that infinite presence.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.84,0:30:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,During that time, I was doing,\Nin some rather intensive spiritual work,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.78,0:30:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and really getting involved in the study of the nature of consciousness itself.\NAnd I started having spontaneous recall of previous lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.12,0:30:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And I can remember all my life I couldn't really dance.\NYou know, it was a terrible ordeal.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.28,0:30:29.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I would, you know, as a kid I took dancing lessons and all that,\Nbut I was terribly awkward and self-conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.16,0:30:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It was painful.\NAnd as I got older, I really didn't like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:34.20,0:30:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't like to dance and would avoid the whole experience if possible,\Nexcept for a slow waltz or a slow foxtrot.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.00,0:30:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But slow waltzes and slow foxtrots were no longer in the mid to late 70s.\NAnd one time I was dancing with someone and she said to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.97,0:30:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, forget about your feet, you know, and just do what my body's doing.\NAnd all of a sudden, in one instant, I could dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.61,0:31:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only could I dance, but I had like unlimited energy to dance.\NI went out every night dancing.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.45,0:31:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I could dance and close up the discos at 2, 3, 4 in the morning,\Nget up at 7 and go to work all day, and I could dance every night.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.39,0:31:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like an unleashed.\NIt's like I wanted to dance for a thousand lifetimes,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.43,0:31:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and finally I could dance again.\NActually, that's what really had happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.97,0:31:30.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I had really condemned myself to no joy for an infinite number of lifetimes\Ndue to a terrible mistake I had made in one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.48,0:31:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, while I was dancing one time, all of a sudden,\Nthe memory of a previous lifetime as a dancer came back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.50,0:31:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't say how long ago it was because it'll stretch my credibility,\Nbut it was a long, long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.28,0:31:52.94,Default,,0,0,0,,But I spontaneously remembered that whole lifetime.\NI remembered being an incredible dancer.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.84,0:31:59.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I danced, I went into a state of high ecstasy.\NI went out the top of the box.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.20,0:32:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And suddenly everything was suffused with life, with light, with life.\NI couldn't breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.22,0:32:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't breathe.\NI felt this incredible joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.88,0:32:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remembered exactly what had gone on.\NIn fact, I was a sacred temple dancer,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.66,0:32:22.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and there were certain inner secrets about this style of dancing\Nthat were part of the sacredness of that spiritual tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.40,0:32:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I went back into that and remembered that lifetime,\Nthe instructions came back to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.10,0:32:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The exact instructions, I remembered them.\NAnd as I remembered the instructions, I began to do them.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.26,0:32:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the dancing was so much fun.\NAnd the dancing now became effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.61,0:32:44.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a certain trick and inner style of dancing\Nin which the body becomes weightless.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.13,0:32:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the body seemed to rotate around an invisible center.\NAnd the more you dance, the more energy you have.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.23,0:32:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the end of four or five hours of dancing,\NI was higher and had more energy than when I had started.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.52,0:33:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So here was a spontaneous recall of a lifetime.\NAnd then I became interested in it as a subject,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.56,0:33:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and of course there are many books and hypnotic techniques\Nand age regression techniques.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.76,0:33:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And I learned a very simple one of self-hypnosis\Nwhere you simply put yourself down, count from one to ten,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:19.27,0:33:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you ask to go back,\Nand you can picture yourself in an elevator
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.27,0:33:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and punch a certain button.\NAnd when you get out, all of a sudden you can re-experience these lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.99,0:33:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And there, one time I did that,\Nand I was caught in a...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.61,0:33:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I was caught in a dilemma about a major decision in life.\NAnd I was very hung up on letting go of a certain piece of property
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.15,0:33:45.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and various things.\NAnd someone had told me, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.38,0:33:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that if you look back in some previous lifetimes,\Nyou would find why you are so hung up.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.52,0:33:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And well, I did.\NAnd suddenly I found myself in another body,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.70,0:33:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,somewhere back in time,\NI would guess around in the 1600s, 1500s.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.90,0:34:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, I found myself, I looked down,\Nand here I had another body.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.28,0:34:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I had huge biceps\Nand a very muscular,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.34,0:34:10.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and I had a leather apron on.\NAnd in my hand was a big hammer,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.34,0:34:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and I realized that I was a blacksmith.\NAnd funny, because in this big house I had built in the East,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.47,0:34:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I was at the very time\Nresearching 16th century blacksmithing shops,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.98,0:34:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was about to make a huge bellows\Nand do my own blacksmithing in the house,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.98,0:34:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,curiously enough.\NBut I developed vibration disease,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.06,0:34:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I couldn't, in my fingertips,\Nand I couldn't do the hammering,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.06,0:34:40.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I was figuring out an electromagnetic hammer,\Nso that I could do blacksmithing, in other words,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.56,0:34:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,without actually having to hit it with a hammer.\NSo anyway, I found myself in this body,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.56,0:34:50.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and there was a portcachere in the house,\Na place where you could drive through with a car.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.56,0:34:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in the reliving of this experience\Nfrom a previous lifetime,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.56,0:35:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this was not gravel,\NI mean, this was not cement, but gravel.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.56,0:35:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I heard the hooves of some oncoming horses,\Nand these four horses with a coach suddenly wheeled,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.56,0:35:11.56,Default,,0,0,0,,came through the portcachere,\Nand apparently the lead horse had thrown a shoe,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.56,0:35:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and the reason they were coming there\Nwas for me to reshoe the horse.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.56,0:35:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But instead of stopping, the horses began to gait,\Nand the front horse went up,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.56,0:35:24.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and he came down, and just as he came down\Nto crush my chest, blank, went out of body.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.56,0:35:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't experience anything.\NThat's curious, I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.35,0:35:35.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just like I became space.\NAnd so I became curious now,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.38,0:35:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and I went back into a lot of lifetimes,\Nand a lot of the ways, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.38,0:35:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at the very end it was not so pleasant, you know.\NStarving to death or dying of thirst or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.38,0:35:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Captured, I mean, I really had some adventurous lifetimes.\NBut all was right at the end,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.77,0:35:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,it would suddenly go blank.\NAnd suddenly it dawned on me,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.77,0:35:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you never experience your own physical death.\NYou never experience it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.77,0:36:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as the bullet that's going to be the one that kills you\Ngets to the heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.77,0:36:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,think, out you go.\NAnd then, of course,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.02,0:36:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,there was the recall of lots of friends of mine.\NA friend of mine remembers being in the Civil War, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.02,0:36:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and he was on the side, I think, of the South, right.\NAnd they're charging with their bayonets,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.02,0:36:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden he's hit by a couple of musket balls,\Nand he goes right on charging.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.02,0:36:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wonders as he's charging,\Nyou know, how he can be charging
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.02,0:36:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,after being hit in the chest with the three musket balls.\NAnd he's charging right ahead,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:34.02,0:36:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,only nobody seemed to be paying any attention to him.\NAnd he looks back,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.02,0:36:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and there's his body laying on the ground,\Nand he realizes he's left it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.02,0:36:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why nobody's paying any attention to him,\Nbecause they don't see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.02,0:36:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that lifetime,\Nhe landed in a hospital
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.02,0:36:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,where he was nursed by someone that he fell in love with.\NHe didn't die.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.02,0:36:57.02,Default,,0,0,0,,He came back in the body,\Nfound himself in a hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:57.02,0:37:00.02,Default,,0,0,0,,and this lovely nurse,\Nand he were attracted to each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.02,0:37:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,but he had other commitments\Nand couldn't be with her in that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.02,0:37:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And curiously enough,\Nhe rejoined her
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.02,0:37:10.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and married her in this lifetime.\NAt about that time in my life,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.50,0:37:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I was studying a certain breathing technique,\Nwhich although I don't advise it,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.50,0:37:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I was researching it at the time.\NAnd in this experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.76,0:37:24.76,Default,,0,0,0,,as one would pass a certain point,\Nsuddenly there was that,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.76,0:37:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not suddenly, but gently and softly,\Nthere was that same experience
Dialogue: 0,0:37:29.76,0:37:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of suddenly leaving the body\Nand no longer experiencing the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.76,0:37:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and repeatedly I would go back\Ninto the same experience which I had
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.76,0:37:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,when I was 14 in the snowbank.\NThe re-experiencing,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.11,0:37:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the forgetting about the body,\Nand as you leave the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.11,0:37:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you forget everything that went with it.\NYou know, within a couple of seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.11,0:37:55.11,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no memory of all that\Nwhat went with that lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.11,0:37:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't remember whether you were married or not married.\NYou have no idea what you did
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.11,0:38:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,or what your name was.\NAll of that becomes ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.11,0:38:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It all becomes irrelevant.\NIt has no bearing in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.11,0:38:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no meaning and no significance\Nand no reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.11,0:38:12.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And instead you begin to experience\Nthat which is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.11,0:38:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,And that same experience\Nof that incredible peace,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.11,0:38:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that incredible lovingness,\Noutside of time and outside of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.46,0:38:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,just pure consciousness and pure awareness,\Njust exquisitely aware of existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.46,0:38:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of the existence of an infinite being\Nthat one is at one with.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.46,0:38:38.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And this experience, I remember one time,\NI had a coach.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.62,0:38:41.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, there was a coach for this experience,\Na rebirther.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.62,0:38:45.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And he was actually a friend of mine\Nand I loved him dearly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.62,0:38:49.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was in this infinite state\Nand I stopped breathing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.62,0:38:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn't want to come back in the body.\NI'd forgotten the body was there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.75,0:38:56.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And so he would say to me,\NBreathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.98,0:38:59.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I didn't want to breathe.\NI didn't need to breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.98,0:39:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There was no desire to breathe\Nbecause where I was
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.98,0:39:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,was so exquisite,\Nso beyond anything this world has to offer,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.98,0:39:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I really had no desire at all to breathe.\NAnd then I heard the incessant appeal in his voice,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.98,0:39:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Please breathe.\NAnd suddenly I realized, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.98,0:39:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,his presence and my love for him.\NAnd therefore out of my love for him,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.98,0:39:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I breathed again.\NBut there I was back in the same experience,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.98,0:39:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,repeatable over and over again,\Njust as it has been described
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.98,0:39:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,by many thousands of people,\Nyou know, throughout man's history,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:36.98,0:39:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but now so available in the literature.\NThat same experience of
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.87,0:39:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,not remembering what you have\Nor what you did, but what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.87,0:39:51.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And so that takes us back then to the board.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.87,0:39:55.87,Default,,0,0,0,,That at the beginning, you know,\Nat the very, not the beginning, excuse me,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.87,0:39:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the bottom of the box,\Nthere is the great concern with havingness.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.87,0:40:05.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And status is based on what you have.\NAnd then as you move up into the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.87,0:40:10.87,Default,,0,0,0,,up into the more powerful centers of courage\Nand capacity and capability,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.87,0:40:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there is a great concern with what you do.\NAnd as you move towards the top of the box,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.03,0:40:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,there is only the awareness\Nand the value of that which you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.03,0:40:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cares what you have anymore.\NNobody cares what you do.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.03,0:40:31.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And so I discovered that when you leave the body,\Nwhat you take with you is what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.03,0:40:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,What you experience is that\Nwhich you've been willing to know
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.03,0:40:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and to own about yourself.\NThe truth about yourself, that which you are,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.06,0:40:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,is what you experience.\NSo all what you had is forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.06,0:40:51.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no memory of money, possessions, power, houses.\NAll that you did is forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.80,0:40:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In that state, if you ask a person, you know,\Nwhat did you do when you thought you were a body
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.80,0:40:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and moved around in the world,\Nthere'd be no recall.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.80,0:41:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere is what you did.\NBut that which you are is overwhelming.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.80,0:41:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That which is is overwhelming.\NAbout the same time,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.73,0:41:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,my mother and I were not too connected about that time\Nbecause she lived in Florida and I was up in New York.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.73,0:41:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And I didn't get a chance to visit her very often.\NAnd we had a difference of opinion about a few things.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.73,0:41:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And so therefore, we weren't like, you know, emotionally close.\NYou might say we were psychically close,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.73,0:41:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,but not emotionally close.\NAnd one day I was out in the woods
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.89,0:41:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden I got an intuitive knowing\Nthat I'd better run down to Florida.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.89,0:41:43.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I got that my mother was dying.\NI got like a call, come down, like right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.24,0:41:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,So I went back in the house and I called up\Nand I made a plane reservation for the next morning
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.34,0:41:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,or the first one out I could get,\Nmaybe the same night, I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.66,0:41:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And after I made the plane reservation,\NI called up and I was told that she was in the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.66,0:42:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, but I knew that she was leaving anyway.\NSo when I got down to Florida,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.66,0:42:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, the heart of Florida, Lakeland,\NLakeland Hospital,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.66,0:42:11.66,Default,,0,0,0,,as I got down there,\NI got a tremendous feeling of relief from my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.66,0:42:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I suddenly felt a great tension relief.\NAnd as I walked into the room,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.66,0:42:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the room was crowded with hospital personnel, you know.\NThere was a big-name specialist from New York
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.66,0:42:27.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and this little hospital was going to make sure\Nthat nothing went wrong, that everything was covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:27.66,0:42:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So the whole staff was practically there.\NAnd there was my mother in an oxygen tank
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.66,0:42:35.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and all kinds of tubes sticking in her all over the place.\NAnd all kinds of meters and electronic things
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.66,0:42:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to make her heart go and all.\NAnd all of a sudden, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:38.66,0:42:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even get into the room.\NThey didn't even know who I was yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.66,0:42:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And I entered the room\Nand I knew that she just left the body.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.66,0:42:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And I experienced a state of absolute ecstasy.\NAs she left the body,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.78,0:42:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,she was so glad to get out of there.\NIt was like an infinite state of joy and ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.78,0:43:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was like one with her in this experience.\NI felt exactly what she was feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.94,0:43:05.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And she was,\Nshe'd waited to leave the body until I got there.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.94,0:43:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And she like joined me.\NBoth of our wills joined to know the experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.94,0:43:20.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She wanted me to experience the experience with her.\NAnd so I experienced that ever-expanding infinite state of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:20.94,0:43:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,She went into a state of absolute ecstasy.\NNobody was ever happy to get out of that body than my mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.94,0:43:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, for years she was hoping to get out of that body.\NWhen she finally got out, boy, was she happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.94,0:43:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course the hospital personnel didn't even know she'd died yet.\NSo telepathically I sent to the cardiologist,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.49,0:43:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, she's dead.\NYou can turn the machine off.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.49,0:43:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So he suddenly got the idea himself and he said,\Nturn off the machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.71,0:43:50.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So he turned off the machine\Nthat was creating the heartbeat and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.71,0:43:54.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And he put the stethoscope to her chest\Nand he said, she's dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:54.71,0:43:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NSo, and then the hospital staff looked at me
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.74,0:44:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,as though they expected me to go into unhappiness or something\Nand I didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.74,0:44:04.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?\NI was in a state of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.74,0:44:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in the same state my mother was.\NI was with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.74,0:44:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What was there to grieve about?\NMy mother was never happier in her life.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.74,0:44:17.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And one woman in the, one woman, she was a nurse's assistant,\Ngot it, an LPN.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.74,0:44:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And she looked at me and she broke into a big grin.\NShe said, boy, was she ever happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.74,0:44:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, you got it.\NShe sure was.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.74,0:44:30.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So the two of us grinned at each other,\Nknowing exactly what was going on, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.74,0:44:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And nobody else really got it.\NThey probably thought I didn't love my mother, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.74,0:44:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and was glad to see her go\Nor I was going to inherit a lot of money or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.74,0:44:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And God knows what their minds thought about it.\NBut we knew what was happening
Dialogue: 0,0:44:43.74,0:44:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and it brought us into that state of joy.\NSo my own experiences, my own memories, my own recall then
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.78,0:44:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was of leaving the body\Nand then there seemed to be two different experiences.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:56.78,0:45:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The one that my mother experienced\Nand which I had experienced so many times
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.78,0:45:04.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of infinite lovingness.\NAnd then there had been those experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:45:04.29,0:45:11.29,Default,,0,0,0,,of going out of body and experiencing nothing.\NWell, either way, you don't experience your physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.29,0:45:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But in the nothing experience,\Nthe next recall would be
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.29,0:45:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I would be back in the body of some other little person,\Nsome other little child.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.29,0:45:23.29,Default,,0,0,0,,In this lifetime, it happened at age three.\NSuddenly it's like wham, you land in the body
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.29,0:45:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,and suddenly anybody who looks back at early childhood\Nwill remember that moment when you suddenly realize
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.29,0:45:36.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that you are, I am, I exist.\NAnd then I realized that I had a belief system going
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.51,0:45:41.51,Default,,0,0,0,,for many years, for many lifetimes.\NIn those lifetimes then,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.51,0:45:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was holding that in mind,\Nthat's what I experienced.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.51,0:45:52.51,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that what you hold in mind,\Nwhat you hold in mind is what you experience in the world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.51,0:45:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what you experience that God is.\NSo the idea that after death there is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.51,0:46:01.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and many people hold that in mind,\Nwhat happens is you go out of body
Dialogue: 0,0:46:01.51,0:46:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and you experience yourself as infinite space.\NNext thing you know, there's another body again.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.28,0:46:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had more often that experience\Nof the infinite presence,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.28,0:46:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the infinite, almost angelic experience.\NAnd as I was looking at that one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:19.28,0:46:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,came back the memories then\Nof being on the other side
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.28,0:46:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and being with those who were dying.\NIt came back first as an experience on battlefields.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.28,0:46:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And I remember being with the dying person\Nand I remember looking at their agony
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.44,0:46:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and their fear and their physical pain\Nand suddenly this infinite lovingness,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.54,0:46:50.54,Default,,0,0,0,,which I was,\Nand at that point formless because,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.54,0:46:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,as I said, in these states of infinite lovingness,\Nthere is no physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.73,0:47:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This infinite state of being with the person dying\Nand then before my very eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.73,0:47:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,they would become transformed.\NThey would like leave the physical body there
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.73,0:47:10.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and all the wounds would heal.\NAnd it was my love,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:10.86,0:47:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,my love joined with the love of God.\NIt was as though I'd turned the heart over to God
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.86,0:47:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and now the energy field of those like angelic beings\Nwho are absolute love poured through.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.86,0:47:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But my consciousness was there\Nwith this dying person.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.18,0:47:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,And the exquisite love\Nof that energy then,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.18,0:47:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,it like healed all the wounds\Nand the fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.18,0:47:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,You would see the fear\Nand the person's eyes would open again
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.18,0:47:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and they would look at you\Nand you could see they were just melting
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.18,0:47:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,with the experience.\NAll the terror dissolved,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.18,0:47:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,all the fear, all the guilt,\Nall the feeling of being separated.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.66,0:48:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,And they would look at you with a recognition.\NAnd then I saw that they would see
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.66,0:48:06.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that which to them was significant or divine.\NThat I myself was formless.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.66,0:48:13.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The same experience has happened in this lifetime.\NWhen you go into higher states of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.78,0:48:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,where you are no longer the physical body\Nand you see that people see
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.78,0:48:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and they see what they are projecting there.\NAnd so being without form,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.78,0:48:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,actually without any form,\Nthe dying person then like opening their eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.78,0:48:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,seeing you as that which would\Nbe most significant to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:34.78,0:48:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes you were seen as\Nthe mother or a lover
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.78,0:48:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,or a crowd of people\Nwith whom the person was dearly in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.78,0:48:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes they would see a divine figure.\NBut this was happening within the phenomena of mind itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.78,0:48:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all the phenomena of mind.\NThe person was experiencing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.78,0:49:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that which was the most healing\Nto them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.39,0:49:05.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And so we come upon a way\Nof overcoming the fear of death.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.39,0:49:08.39,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NOvercoming the fear of death
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.39,0:49:13.39,Default,,0,0,0,,is the willingness to be that\Nto yourself and to others who are dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.39,0:49:20.42,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to overcome your own fear of death\Nis to picture yourself as on the other side.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.42,0:49:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a first aid receiving station.\NAnd you open your heart and you ask
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.42,0:49:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,to be connected with those angelic forces.\NTo become one with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:29.42,0:49:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And now you picture yourself\Ngoing to those who are dying.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.58,0:49:37.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You do it now while you are still\Nin your own physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.58,0:49:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,But you send forth that energy of compassion.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.58,0:49:46.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Consciousness doesn't know about bodies.\NBodies have to do with the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.58,0:49:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,a limited viewpoint.\NYou send forth this energy field of compassion.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.71,0:49:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And you picture yourself in your imagination.\NYou begin it with your imagination now.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.71,0:50:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,With any person because\Nin any one hour
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.71,0:50:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,there are over 5 billion people on the planet.\NHow many people do you think are dying every hour?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.71,0:50:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands and thousands.\NBy the time we finish this talk
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.71,0:50:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,easily 15 or 20 thousand people have died.\NAnd what you do is you select somebody
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.13,0:50:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,that you feel you could be most loving.\NA child in a crib.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.13,0:50:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A teenage child just hit by a car.\NSomebody on a battlefield riddled with bullets.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:25.96,0:50:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A mother in childbirth.\NA person committing suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.96,0:50:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Picture the person for whom you have the most compassion\Nand start with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.98,0:50:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And send yourself forth in your imagination to that person.\NAnd now picture yourself as infinitely loving.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.98,0:50:50.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in a way you are more alone\Nand yet more not alone than ever before.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.26,0:50:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because you can fully express\Nall the tenderness and love
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.26,0:51:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that you have suppressed your whole lifetime.\NNow is your chance to send it forth
Dialogue: 0,0:51:00.26,0:51:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and to be with that person.\NAnd think of the agony and the fear
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.26,0:51:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,of so many people.\NAnd what you do is you go to them
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.26,0:51:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to heal them.\NPicture yourself holding them in your arms.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.26,0:51:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And now the love pours forth through your heart.\NIt really comes from a higher being
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.26,0:51:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and radiates out through your heart.\NIt suffuses that person
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.26,0:51:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and you begin to see their fear melt away.\NAnd many people as they die
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.46,0:51:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,whatever the apprehension was before\Nyou will notice go into profound states
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.46,0:51:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of serenity.\NAs though that compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.46,0:51:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from the great beings of the world\Nreaches forth to us
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.68,0:51:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,at our moment of greatest need.\NAnd so when the person says
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.68,0:51:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh God help me\Nbecause this is a world
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.68,0:51:51.68,Default,,0,0,0,,a universe of free will.\NThen they open the door to this compassion
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.68,0:51:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is being radiated forth by others\Nand now by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.68,0:51:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And so you are by their side\Nand in every way possible
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.68,0:52:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,you nurture them\Nand heal them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.68,0:52:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You reach out to them\Nand gently lift them out of their body.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.68,0:52:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,That they are safe.\NThey are home.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.68,0:52:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They are cared for.\NThey are greatly loved by God.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.68,0:52:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They begin to get the inner experience\Nof this truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.68,0:52:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You put your personal self aside\Nbecause your personal self is not needed here.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.68,0:52:25.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no need for your personality\Nwith its likes and its dislikes
Dialogue: 0,0:52:25.68,0:52:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,its aversions and its attractions.\NJust be that individual
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.68,0:52:36.68,Default,,0,0,0,,with the energy which flows forth through the heart.\NAnd what happens is that healing energy now
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.68,0:52:39.68,Default,,0,0,0,,through your willingness\Nflows through you
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.68,0:52:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and into the being of the other person.\NAnd you see the transformation before your very eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.68,0:52:49.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You literally see it.\NYou see the fear leave their eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.68,0:52:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the painful tension leave their body.\NAnd you begin to experience
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.68,0:53:00.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that the pain is leaving their body.\NAnd they go into that same state of infinite peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.68,0:53:04.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrounded by this light.\NSurrounded by this love.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.68,0:53:09.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Feeling complete and total and healed.\NNo more fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.68,0:53:12.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No more separation.\NNo more guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.68,0:53:16.68,Default,,0,0,0,,No more anxiety.\NAnd what happens is the two of you together
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.68,0:53:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,are lifted.\NLifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.68,0:53:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The two of you right out of the body.\NTogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.22,0:53:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I had this very same experience not long ago.\NA few months ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.42,0:53:35.74,Default,,0,0,0,,When I suddenly, accidentally with a saw\Nchopped off this thumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.74,0:53:39.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And at first I heard\Nfirst there was shock.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:39.74,0:53:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,But in this shock there was suddenly like a chorus in my mind.\NAs though I was surrounded
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.62,0:53:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,by angelic forces.\NAnd they kept chanting to me
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.62,0:53:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,as though I'd forgotten.\NYou're not a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.75,0:53:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're totally free.\NYou're not a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.75,0:53:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,You're totally free.\NAnd this chant kept going all the way to the hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.75,0:54:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the hospital because of various things\NI had to have you know an operation now.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:06.10,0:54:11.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I cannot take any kind of anesthetic or analgesic.\NSo it had to be done without anesthesia
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.10,0:54:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,or without analgesia.\NAnd the surgeon was a little apprehensive about this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.10,0:54:19.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And I told him well I know a way of\Nhandling this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.10,0:54:21.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You just go right ahead.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.14,0:54:26.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I lay back and friends of mine\Nand people very close to me were praying for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.14,0:54:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And they had gathered around and\NI lay back and I began to just surrender.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.94,0:54:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,See?\NAll of this is surrender is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.94,0:54:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The surrender of the personal will\Nand the asking of God to reveal to you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.94,0:54:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the truth of that which is.\NAnd as I surrendered
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.26,0:54:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,then I had that same profound experience.\NAs though I was picked up by angelic forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.26,0:55:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Lifted so softly that feathers would seem rough by comparison.\NLifted gently although the body was there
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.26,0:55:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,it was like I no longer experienced it.\NInstead I went into a state of infinite and profound peace
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.26,0:55:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond all description.\NAn infinite inner joy and happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.26,0:55:15.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be described.\NAnd I remember in my mind
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.93,0:55:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I was looking at the thumb\Nor some representation of that thumb on a different plane
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.93,0:55:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and I felt happy at it being removed\Nbecause it symbolized something I wished to be rid of.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.93,0:55:36.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of the spiritual symbology of it.\NAnd so what could have been an excruciating painful experience
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.34,0:55:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,instead was ecstatic.\NNot that jumping up and down kind of ecstasy
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.34,0:55:47.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but an exquisite knowingness\Nsurrounded by infinite peace
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.34,0:55:53.34,Default,,0,0,0,,infinitely protected by the love of the universe\Ninfinitely protected by God
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.34,0:55:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the representation of God in my inner experience.\NAnd so now when we look at
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.50,0:56:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,what is the dying experience we see?\NIt's a surrender and it's a letting go.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:05.50,0:56:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a willingness to open one's heart\Nto be love to others.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.50,0:56:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're contemplating dying\Nand if you're doing the things I'm talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.50,0:56:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,if in the morning when you get up\Nyou say to God
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.50,0:56:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to those who are dying I send my consciousness\NI send my love
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.50,0:56:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,my willingness to be one with them\Nit's like the forces of the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:56:28.50,0:56:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,then use the power of your consciousness\Nand literally carry it to the extreme.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:32.50,0:56:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great person.\NAt first it will seem to you like imagination
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.24,0:56:44.62,Default,,0,0,0,,it will seem like something that you are doing\Nbut after you do this a few times
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.62,0:56:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize you will suddenly experience\Nthat you are not doing this anymore
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.62,0:56:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're saying yes to it\Nit is now being done through you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.62,0:56:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it is being done through you\Nyou yourself go into a state of high joy and ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:58.62,0:57:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that what the world calls your physical body is leaving\Nno longer is even important.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.62,0:57:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And I've been in those states\Nwhere I literally felt the energy coming through
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.62,0:57:15.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and going to people who were in automobile accidents\Nhere in Arizona.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.62,0:57:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going down I-17\Nand I feel this profound energy go through me
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.66,0:57:25.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and it like goes through the heart\Nand this profound sense of loving power
Dialogue: 0,0:57:25.69,0:57:31.69,Default,,0,0,0,,which bypassed my personal self\Nand it went down the highway about a mile or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.69,0:57:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I got around the bend in the highway\NI wondered where this energy was going.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.69,0:57:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Here was a car upside down\Nit had just crashed
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.69,0:57:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and its wheels in fact were still spinning.\NAnd inside were people severely injured
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.69,0:57:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and I heard them praying out to God.\NIt's as though you were a traveling antenna
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.14,0:57:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and God used you as an antenna tower\Nto radiate this energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.14,0:58:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And curiously enough that same day\Nabout five miles down the highway
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.14,0:58:04.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it began to happen again.\NThat same powerful energy came through me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:04.14,0:58:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It's happened over and over again\Non the streets of Chicago
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.14,0:58:12.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and all over the world.\NBut as I'm driving down I-17
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.14,0:58:16.14,Default,,0,0,0,,it started again.\NAnd this time it also went down the road ahead of me
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.14,0:58:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and when I came around the bend\Nthere was a second accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:20.14,0:58:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Another car had just turned over.\NThis time there was a squad car there.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.14,0:58:28.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And as I went past\Nthis energy kept flowing backwards now
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.14,0:58:32.14,Default,,0,0,0,,to the site of the accident\Nand it continued on for some miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.14,0:58:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then it slowly came to a stop\Nas though the person had now connected
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.14,0:58:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,with a more infinite energy field.\NAnd what was my inner state?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.84,0:58:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What was my feeling about myself and my body?\NI forgot that I had a body.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.84,0:58:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it was living or dying was so irrelevant.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.84,0:58:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the joy of this experience is overwhelming.\NThe willingness to be that to others then.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.84,0:59:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The forgetting about the personal self.\NAllow your consciousness and your energy
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.84,0:59:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to be used by those angels.\NBy those angelic forces.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.84,0:59:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You see our infinite self is everything.\NIt's connected with the angelic realms.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.84,0:59:14.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We own that angelic condition within us.\NThat we ourselves have the capacity to join
Dialogue: 0,0:59:14.84,0:59:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,by our willingness, by our saying yes\Nto allow ourselves to surrender
Dialogue: 0,0:59:19.84,0:59:25.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to their energy to go to the dead and the dying.\NAnd now we see that there is no such thing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.87,0:59:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,as death or dying.\NYou see?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.87,0:59:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why we talked about letting go of the body\Nand saying farewell to it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.87,0:59:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Because life goes to life.\NLife never stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:35.87,0:59:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If it leaves this body you barely notice it\Nbecause you're so busy being with others
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.87,0:59:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,that you hardly notice that the physical body\Nthat the planet said belonged to it
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.87,0:59:48.87,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't even exist anymore.\NThere's stories of yogis who've been back and forth
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.87,0:59:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,on the planet in three different bodies\Nand never even noticed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.61,1:00:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Beyond the experience of the physical body\Nan experience which is so difficult to describe
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.23,1:00:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,because tears are part of the body.\NAre part of the experience of the memory.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.94,1:00:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It's exquisite beauty.\NAnd so what we prepare ourself then
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.32,1:00:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,is for an experience of exquisite beauty.\NBecause it is the most beautiful of all experiences.
